                    '4' => 'Thorough lock safety management: formally communicates to the lock operator that as Master of an ADN vessel carrying flammable cargo, consent for the manual override is conditional on a written risk assessment and specific safety measures, requires: (a) detailed briefing on the manual override procedure from the lock maintenance team, (b) confirmation that any gate movement will be controlled and gradual with the ability to stop at any point, (c) fire brigade on standby at the lock before any attempt, (d) all crew at emergency stations with personal gas monitors, (e) cargo tank vapour recovery systems active, (f) emergency egress route identified (lock ladder access to the top), stipulates go/no-go criteria for the manual override attempt, prepares the vessel for emergency departure if the gate does open — engine ready, lines singled up.',
