                    '4' => 'Systematic failure response: immediately reduces speed to the minimum safe steerage way for the current (approximately 8-9 km/h through water to maintain 3-4 km/h over ground downstream). Activates all alternative navigation aids: echo sounder on continuous monitoring, radar at maximum detail settings for channel identification, searchlights to identify bank markers and buoys visually. Uses the backup ECDIS as a general reference only — cross-references every buoy position shown on the outdated chart with radar and visual observation. Contacts viadonau vessel traffic service and RIS immediately, reporting the ECDIS failure and requesting navigational guidance through the Wachau section. Requests specific information on current buoy positions and any hazards. Considers the cruise ship ahead as a general channel indicator but maintains a safe following distance (minimum 400-500m). Assigns the lookout to continuous visual watch with searchlight for bank markers, buoys, and channel edges.',
